title: Registered Entity
description: Any legal entity created through an act of official registration. In most cases, registered entities will have an official issued identifier.

title: Legal entity
description: A body with distinct legal personality, such as an international institution, but which is not otherwise uniquely identified in some official register.

title: Arrangement
description: An artificial entity, created by agreements, contracts or other processes.

title: Anonymous entity
description: An entity that has been identified, but for which no identifying information is being published.

title: Unknown entity
description: An entity that has not been identified.

title: State
description: A country, nation or community with legal sovereignty within a territory.

title: State body
description: An administrative or legislative unit within a state's apparatus.
